# Rewrite Testing Strategy

Applies to `next/nlrc_vksplat/` and `test_data/`. Use data-driven GPU validation; do not mock shader behavior.

## Philosophy

- Not TDD: do not require tests before the minimal Vulkan harness or pipeline code exists.
- Fixture-first and stage-isolated: each compute dispatch from `ref/docs/shader-pipeline.md` is ported and verified before wiring the parent subgraph.
- Goldens are not universal ground truth. They encode frozen ref behavior, including quirks; invariants catch impossible or ref-internal bugs.

## Testing Report Contract

`next/nlrc_vksplat/docs/testing-report.md` is the coverage, gap, and hardening source of truth.

Update it whenever a change:

- adds, removes, renames, or materially changes tests;
- changes what a fixture or golden validates;
- changes `test_data/generate_fixtures.py`, fixture catalog validation, GPU policy, or CTest registration;
- claims a gap is now covered, blocked, avoided, or deferred.

Do not mark behavior covered unless it is asserted by CTest or a documented dedicated validation workflow.

## Oracles

| Oracle | Purpose | Required |
|--------|---------|----------|
| Invariant | Mathematical/logical properties without ref output | When cheap |
| Ref parity golden | Match frozen baseline `ref-baseline-2026-06-12` | Every ported dispatch |
| E2E smoke | Tiny scene and loss/PSNR trend | Later, not per-stage |

## CMake and CTest

| Target / command | Role |
|------------------|------|
| `nlrc_vksplat_tests` | Catch2 executable |
| `nlrc_vksplat_test_support` | Shared fixture, golden, GPU-policy, and manifest helpers |
| `nlrc_vksplat_gpu` | Headless Vulkan substrate for tests and future pipeline code |
| `ctest --preset windows-debug --output-on-failure` | Run discovered tests |
| `test_data/generate_fixtures.py --check` | Verify checked-in generated fixture/golden files are reproducible |
| `nlrc_vksplat_fixture_generation_check` | CTest wrapper around fixture-generation drift checks |

Options:

- `NLRC_VKSPLAT_BUILD_TESTS`: default `ON` on Windows and `OFF` on `ohos-*` cross-builds.
- `NLRC_VKSPLAT_GPU_TESTS`: `AUTO`, `REQUIRE`, or `OFF`.
- `NLRC_VKSPLAT_TEST_DATA_DIR`: compile definition pointing at repo-root `test_data/`.

## Catch2 Tags and GPU Policy

| Tag | Behavior |
|-----|----------|
| `[host]` | Always runs fixture I/O, compare helpers, and manifest profile checks |
| `[gpu]` | Requires a Vulkan compute device |

In `AUTO`, `[gpu]` tests call `SKIP` when `gpu_available()` is false. `REQUIRE` fails the run. `OFF` skips all `[gpu]` tests.

Use `NLRC_REQUIRE_GPU()` at the start of GPU test cases.

## Harness API

| API | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `load_fixture_manifest(path)` | Parse `manifest.json` into typed specs |
| `BufferSpec` | Per-buffer `file`, `shape`, `dtype`, and `epsilon` |
| `BufferDtype` | Supported manifest dtypes: `Float32`, `UInt32`, `Int32`, `Int64` |
| `load_fixture_buffer<T>(fixture_root, manifest, buffer_name)` | Load named `.bin` with dtype and byte-size checks |
| `compare_float_buffers(Span<const float>, Span<const float>, epsilon)` | Golden compare, default `1e-5` |
| `assert_no_nan_inf(Span<const float>)` | Sanity oracle helper |
| `manifest_matches_build_profile(manifest)` | `emulate_int64` / `emulate_f32_atomic` vs compiled profile |

Per-dispatch workflow: load fixture, upload `StorageBuffer`, bind `StorageBindingList`, dispatch `ComputePipeline`, read back, then assert invariants and/or golden parity.

## Porting Workflow Per Dispatch

1. Add or update the logical shader entry in `next/nlrc_vksplat/src/gpu/shader_descriptors.hpp`; this is the rewrite binding source of truth.
2. Add or update the typed storage-binding resolver helper in `shader_binding_resolver.hpp`; helper field order must match the registry entry.
3. Add fixture catalog routing in `tests/support/shader_fixture_mapping.cpp`, or add an explicit composite fixture contract for host-helper pipelines that are not one logical shader.
4. Add or update synthetic fixture values in `test_data/generate_fixtures.py`, or document why a curated ref-derived fixture is maintained separately.
5. Ensure fixture `manifest.json` `bindings[]` matches the registry entry or composite fixture contract, then regenerate checked-in fixture/golden manifests and `.bin` payloads with `generate_fixtures.py --write`.
6. Verify fixture generation with `generate_fixtures.py --check`; CTest also runs this through `nlrc_vksplat_fixture_generation_check`.
7. Add invariant Catch2 tests where applicable, and add golden parity tests loading `test_data/golden_masters/...`.
8. Document fixture and golden meaning in `test_data/README.md`, including exact values for small synthetic buffers.
9. Update `next/nlrc_vksplat/docs/testing-report.md` for new coverage, changed test behavior, or remaining gaps.
10. Implement the stage in `next/nlrc_vksplat/` until tests pass, then integrate into the parent subgraph or training path.

## test_data Layout

```text
test_data/
  generate_fixtures.py
  fixtures/
    <group>/<case>/
      manifest.json
      *.bin
  golden_masters/
    <group>/<case>/
      manifest.json
      *.bin
```

Groups: `harness`, `cumsum`, `sum`, `where`, `radix_sort`. Manifest `stage_name` stays globally unique; tests resolve paths by scanning manifests.

Each `manifest.json` records:

- `ref_baseline_tag`, `stage_name`, `subgraph`, `bindings`
- `buffers`, `shapes`, `dtypes`
- `cmake_preset`, `emulate_int64`, `emulate_f32_atomic`
- `notes`
- for goldens, optional `vkbd_source` and per-buffer `epsilon`

Default profile is `windows-debug` with both emulate flags `0`.

Use `test_data/README.md` as the fixture catalog. Add per-fixture Markdown only when a future large ref-generated fixture cannot be summarized clearly in the central README. Use `testing-report.md` for coverage and gap status, not fixture value catalogs.

## Fixture Sources

- Synthetic fixtures: edit `test_data/generate_fixtures.py`; checked-in `.bin` and `manifest.json` files are generated outputs.
- Verify synthetic fixture drift with `test_data/generate_fixtures.py --check`; CTest also runs `nlrc_vksplat_fixture_generation_check`.
- Ref-derived fixtures: generate source material from ref with `VKSPLAT_ENABLE_BUFFER_DUMPS=ON`, inspect with `ref/vksplat/scripts/vkbd_tool.py`, and convert curated buffers with `next/nlrc_vksplat/scripts/vkbd_to_bins.py`.
- Do not commit full training-run dumps; commit minimal curated sets only.

## Invariant Examples

| Category | Examples |
|----------|----------|
| Sort / radix | permutation of keys, stability, empty/single element, duplicate keys |
| Prefix sum / cumsum | `out[i] == sum(in[0..i])` for small host-verified inputs |
| Projection | single splat plus known camera gives bounded tile count / rect |
| Sanity | no NaN/Inf, shapes match docs, zero-count early exits |
| OHOS | re-run same fixture on `ohos-debug` after Windows passes |

## Updating Goldens

- Allowed with explicit commit reason: ref baseline bump, intentional behavior fix, or documented ref bug.
- Never silently widen epsilon or shrink fixtures to make tests pass.
- If invariant and golden disagree, investigate before assuming ref is correct.
